{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "c3d4e5f6-a7b8-9012-cdef-123456789012",
    "name": "OIDC OAuth 1o1 — OAuth",
    "description": "OAuth 2.0 / OIDC endpoints — discovery, JWKS, authorization code flow, token exchange, and userinfo.\n\nMounted at `/`.\n\n**Typical Authorization Code + PKCE flow:**\n1. **OIDC Discovery** — inspect server capabilities (optional)\n2. **Authorize** — redirect the user; server redirects back with `?code=...`\n3. Paste the returned `code` into the `authCode` collection variable\n4. **Token — Authorization Code** — exchange the code for tokens; `accessToken` and `idToken` are saved automatically\n5. **UserInfo** — call with the saved `accessToken`\n\nSet `baseUrl`, `clientId`, `redirectUri`, `codeVerifier`, and `codeChallenge` before running.\n\n> **PKCE helper:** generate a `code_verifier` (random 43–128 char string) and its SHA-256 base64url `code_challenge` with any PKCE tool (e.g. https://tonyxu-io.github.io/pkce-generator/).",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "variable": [
    {
      "key": "baseUrl",
      "value": "http://localhost:8000",
      "type": "string",
      "description": "Base URL of the API server"
    },
    {
      "key": "clientId",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string",
      "description": "Public client_id of your registered OAuth client (cid_...)"
    },
    {
      "key": "clientSecret",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string",
      "description": "Client secret — required for CONFIDENTIAL clients; leave empty for PUBLIC clients"
    },
    {
      "key": "redirectUri",
      "value": "http://localhost:3000/callback",
      "type": "string",
      "description": "Must exactly match one of the client's registered redirect URIs"
    },
    {
      "key": "codeVerifier",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string",
      "description": "PKCE code_verifier — random 43-128 char string you generate before starting the flow"
    },
    {
      "key": "codeChallenge",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string",
      "description": "PKCE code_challenge — SHA-256 base64url of the code_verifier"
    },
    {
      "key": "authCode",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string",
      "description": "Authorization code returned by the /authorize redirect — paste it here"
    },
    {
      "key": "accessToken",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string",
      "description": "Populated automatically after a successful token exchange"
    },
    {
      "key": "idToken",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string",
      "description": "Populated automatically after a successful token exchange (OIDC ID token)"
    },
    {
      "key": "oauthRefreshToken",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string",
      "description": "Populated automatically after a successful token exchange with offline_access scope"
    }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "Discovery",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "OIDC Discovery",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status is 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "const res = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('Has authorization_endpoint', () => pm.expect(res).to.have.property('authorization_endpoint'));",
                  "pm.test('Has token_endpoint', () => pm.expect(res).to.have.property('token_endpoint'));",
                  "pm.test('Has jwks_uri', () => pm.expect(res).to.have.property('jwks_uri'));",
                  "pm.test('Has userinfo_endpoint', () => pm.expect(res).to.have.property('userinfo_endpoint'));"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/.well-known/openid-configuration",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": [".well-known", "openid-configuration"]
            },
            "description": "Returns the OpenID Connect Discovery document describing all server endpoints, supported scopes, response types, and signing algorithms.\n\nPublic — no authentication required. Clients can use this to auto-configure themselves.\n\n**Key fields returned:**\n- `authorization_endpoint`\n- `token_endpoint`\n- `userinfo_endpoint`\n- `jwks_uri`\n- `scopes_supported`\n- `code_challenge_methods_supported`"
          },
          "response": [
            {
              "name": "200 OK",
              "status": "OK",
              "code": 200,
              "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
              "body": "{\n  \"issuer\": \"http://localhost:8000\",\n  \"authorization_endpoint\": \"http://localhost:8000/oauth/authorize\",\n  \"token_endpoint\": \"http://localhost:8000/oauth/token\",\n  \"userinfo_endpoint\": \"http://localhost:8000/oauth/userinfo\",\n  \"jwks_uri\": \"http://localhost:8000/oauth/jwks.json\",\n  \"scopes_supported\": [\"openid\", \"profile\", \"email\"],\n  \"response_types_supported\": [\"code\"],\n  \"grant_types_supported\": [\"authorization_code\", \"client_credentials\", \"refresh_token\"],\n  \"token_endpoint_auth_methods_supported\": [\"client_secret_basic\", \"client_secret_post\", \"none\"],\n  \"claims_supported\": [\"sub\", \"iss\", \"aud\", \"exp\", \"iat\", \"email\", \"given_name\", \"family_name\"],\n  \"code_challenge_methods_supported\": [\"plain\", \"S256\"]\n}"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "JWKS",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status is 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "const res = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('Has keys array', () => pm.expect(res).to.have.property('keys').that.is.an('array'));",
                  "pm.test('Key has kty field', () => pm.expect(res.keys[0]).to.have.property('kty'));"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/jwks.json",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["jwks.json"]
            },
            "description": "Returns the JSON Web Key Set (JWKS) — the public keys used to verify tokens issued by this server.\n\nPublic — no authentication required. Resource servers use this endpoint to validate access tokens and ID tokens.\n\n**Returned key fields:** `kty`, `use`, `alg`, `kid`, `n`, `e` (RSA) or `x`, `y`, `crv` (EC)."
          },
          "response": [
            {
              "name": "200 OK",
              "status": "OK",
              "code": 200,
              "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
              "body": "{\n  \"keys\": [\n    {\n      \"kty\": \"RSA\",\n      \"use\": \"sig\",\n      \"alg\": \"RS256\",\n      \"kid\": \"key-id-here\",\n      \"n\": \"base64url-modulus\",\n      \"e\": \"AQAB\"\n    }\n  ]\n}"
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Authorization Code Flow",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Authorize (browser redirect)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "prerequest",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "// PKCE reminder",
                  "if (!pm.collectionVariables.get('codeVerifier')) {",
                  "  console.warn('codeVerifier is not set. Generate a PKCE pair and set codeVerifier + codeChallenge before sending.');",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            },
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "// The server responds with a 302 redirect — Postman follows it to the login page",
                  "// or redirects straight to redirect_uri with ?code=... if already authenticated.",
                  "// Copy the 'code' query param from the redirect URL and paste it into the authCode variable.",
                  "pm.test('Status is 302 (redirect) or 200', () => {",
                  "  pm.expect(pm.response.code).to.be.oneOf([200, 302]);",
                  "});"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/authorize?client_id={{clientId}}&redirect_uri={{redirectUri}}&response_type=code&scope=openid profile email offline_access&state=random-state-value&code_challenge={{codeChallenge}}&code_challenge_method=S256&nonce=random-nonce-value",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["authorize"],
              "query": [
                { "key": "client_id", "value": "{{clientId}}", "description": "Your registered client_id" },
                { "key": "redirect_uri", "value": "{{redirectUri}}", "description": "Must match a registered redirect URI exactly" },
                { "key": "response_type", "value": "code", "description": "Only 'code' is supported" },
                { "key": "scope", "value": "openid profile email offline_access", "description": "Space-separated requested scopes (include offline_access for refresh tokens)" },
                { "key": "state", "value": "random-state-value", "description": "CSRF protection token — verify it matches in the callback" },
                { "key": "code_challenge", "value": "{{codeChallenge}}", "description": "PKCE code_challenge (base64url SHA-256 of code_verifier)" },
                { "key": "code_challenge_method", "value": "S256", "description": "'S256' (recommended) or 'plain'" },
                { "key": "nonce", "value": "random-nonce-value", "description": "Optional — included in the ID token to prevent replay attacks" }
              ]
            },
            "description": "Initiates the Authorization Code + PKCE flow.\n\n**How to use this in Postman:**\n1. Set `clientId`, `codeChallenge`, and `redirectUri` collection variables.\n2. Send this request — if the user is not logged in, the server redirects to `/login`.\n3. After login (via the browser), the server redirects to `redirect_uri?code=...&state=...`.\n4. Copy the `code` value from the redirect URL and paste it into the `authCode` collection variable.\n5. Run the **Token — Authorization Code** request.\n\n**Required params:** `client_id`, `redirect_uri`, `response_type=code`, `code_challenge`, `code_challenge_method`\n\n**Optional params:** `scope`, `state`, `nonce`\n\n> ⚠️ This endpoint performs a redirect — it is best tested in a browser or with Postman's \"Follow redirects\" setting disabled so you can inspect the Location header."
          },
          "response": [
            {
              "name": "302 Found — Redirect to login (unauthenticated)",
              "status": "Found",
              "code": 302,
              "header": [
                { "key": "Location", "value": "/login?returnTo=%2Fauthorize%3Fclient_id%3D..." }
              ],
              "body": ""
            },
            {
              "name": "302 Found — Redirect to client with code (authenticated)",
              "status": "Found",
              "code": 302,
              "header": [
                { "key": "Location", "value": "http://localhost:3000/callback?code=auth_code_here&state=random-state-value" }
              ],
              "body": ""
            },
            {
              "name": "400 Bad Request — Validation error",
              "status": "Bad Request",
              "code": 400,
              "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
              "body": "{\n  \"success\": false,\n  \"error\": {\n    \"code\": \"VALIDATION_ERROR\",\n    \"message\": \"redirect_uri: redirect_uri must be a valid URL\"\n  }\n}"
            },
            {
              "name": "400 Bad Request — Invalid client_id",
              "status": "Bad Request",
              "code": 400,
              "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
              "body": "{\n  \"success\": false,\n  \"error\": {\n    \"code\": \"BAD_REQUEST\",\n    \"message\": \"Invalid client_id\"\n  }\n}"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Token — Authorization Code",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status is 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "const res = pm.response.json();",
                  "if (res.access_token) {",
                  "  pm.collectionVariables.set('accessToken', res.access_token);",
                  "  console.log('accessToken saved:', res.access_token);",
                  "}",
                  "if (res.id_token) {",
                  "  pm.collectionVariables.set('idToken', res.id_token);",
                  "  console.log('idToken saved:', res.id_token);",
                  "}",
                  "if (res.refresh_token) {",
                  "  pm.collectionVariables.set('oauthRefreshToken', res.refresh_token);",
                  "  console.log('oauthRefreshToken saved:', res.refresh_token);",
                  "}",
                  "pm.test('Has access_token', () => pm.expect(res).to.have.property('access_token'));",
                  "pm.test('Has token_type bearer', () => pm.expect(res.token_type).to.eql('Bearer'));",
                  "pm.test('Has id_token (OIDC)', () => pm.expect(res).to.have.property('id_token'));"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "auth": { "type": "noauth" },
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/x-www-form-urlencoded" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "urlencoded",
              "urlencoded": [
                { "key": "grant_type", "value": "authorization_code", "description": "Must be 'authorization_code'" },
                { "key": "code", "value": "{{authCode}}", "description": "The authorization code from the /authorize redirect" },
                { "key": "redirect_uri", "value": "{{redirectUri}}", "description": "Must match the redirect_uri used in /authorize exactly" },
                { "key": "client_id", "value": "{{clientId}}", "description": "Your client_id" },
                { "key": "client_secret", "value": "{{clientSecret}}", "description": "Your client_secret — omit for PUBLIC clients" },
                { "key": "code_verifier", "value": "{{codeVerifier}}", "description": "The original PKCE code_verifier (pre-hash value)" }
              ]
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/token",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["token"]
            },
            "description": "Exchange the authorization code for tokens.\n\n**Requires:** `grant_type=authorization_code`, `code`, `redirect_uri`, `client_id`, `code_verifier`\n\n**Client authentication options:**\n- **Body params** — send `client_id` + `client_secret` in the request body (used here)\n- **Basic Auth** — send `Authorization: Basic base64(client_id:client_secret)` header instead\n- **No secret** — PUBLIC clients omit `client_secret` entirely\n\nThe test script automatically saves `accessToken`, `idToken`, and `oauthRefreshToken` into collection variables.\n\n> The server sets `Cache-Control: no-store` and `Pragma: no-cache` headers on this response per the OAuth 2.0 spec."
          },
          "response": [
            {
              "name": "200 OK — Tokens issued",
              "status": "OK",
              "code": 200,
              "header": [
                { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" },
                { "key": "Cache-Control", "value": "no-store" },
                { "key": "Pragma", "value": "no-cache" }
              ],
              "body": "{\n  \"access_token\": \"eyJhbGciOiJSUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9...\",\n  \"token_type\": \"Bearer\",\n  \"expires_in\": 3600,\n  \"refresh_token\": \"rt_xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx\",\n  \"id_token\": \"eyJhbGciOiJSUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9...\",\n  \"scope\": \"openid profile email\"\n}"
            },
            {
              "name": "400 Bad Request — Missing code_verifier",
              "status": "Bad Request",
              "code": 400,
              "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
              "body": "{\n  \"success\": false,\n  \"error\": {\n    \"code\": \"BAD_REQUEST\",\n    \"message\": \"Missing code, redirect_uri, or code_verifier\"\n  }\n}"
            },
            {
              "name": "400 Bad Request — Unsupported grant_type",
              "status": "Bad Request",
              "code": 400,
              "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
              "body": "{\n  \"success\": false,\n  \"error\": {\n    \"code\": \"BAD_REQUEST\",\n    \"message\": \"Unsupported grant_type: implicit\"\n  }\n}"
            },
            {
              "name": "401 Unauthorized — Invalid client credentials",
              "status": "Unauthorized",
              "code": 401,
              "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
              "body": "{\n  \"success\": false,\n  \"error\": {\n    \"code\": \"INVALID_CLIENT\",\n    \"message\": \"Missing client_id\"\n  }\n}"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Token — Authorization Code (Basic Auth)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status is 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "const res = pm.response.json();",
                  "if (res.access_token) {",
                  "  pm.collectionVariables.set('accessToken', res.access_token);",
                  "  console.log('accessToken saved:', res.access_token);",
                  "}",
                  "pm.test('Has access_token', () => pm.expect(res).to.have.property('access_token'));"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "auth": {
              "type": "basic",
              "basic": [
                { "key": "username", "value": "{{clientId}}", "type": "string" },
                { "key": "password", "value": "{{clientSecret}}", "type": "string" }
              ]
            },
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/x-www-form-urlencoded" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "urlencoded",
              "urlencoded": [
                { "key": "grant_type", "value": "authorization_code" },
                { "key": "code", "value": "{{authCode}}" },
                { "key": "redirect_uri", "value": "{{redirectUri}}" },
                { "key": "code_verifier", "value": "{{codeVerifier}}" }
              ]
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/token",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["token"]
            },
            "description": "Same as **Token — Authorization Code** but uses HTTP Basic Auth (`Authorization: Basic base64(client_id:client_secret)`) instead of body params.\n\nThe `client_id` and `client_secret` collection variables are used automatically by the Basic Auth configuration."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Token — Refresh Token",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status is 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "const res = pm.response.json();",
                  "if (res.access_token) {",
                  "  pm.collectionVariables.set('accessToken', res.access_token);",
                  "  console.log('accessToken updated:', res.access_token);",
                  "}",
                  "if (res.id_token) {",
                  "  pm.collectionVariables.set('idToken', res.id_token);",
                  "  console.log('idToken updated:', res.id_token);",
                  "}",
                  "if (res.refresh_token) {",
                  "  pm.collectionVariables.set('oauthRefreshToken', res.refresh_token);",
                  "  console.log('oauthRefreshToken rotated:', res.refresh_token);",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "auth": { "type": "noauth" },
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/x-www-form-urlencoded" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "urlencoded",
              "urlencoded": [
                { "key": "grant_type", "value": "refresh_token", "description": "Must be 'refresh_token'" },
                { "key": "refresh_token", "value": "{{oauthRefreshToken}}", "description": "The refresh token to rotate" },
                { "key": "client_id", "value": "{{clientId}}", "description": "Your client_id" },
                { "key": "client_secret", "value": "{{clientSecret}}", "description": "Your client_secret — omit for PUBLIC clients" }
              ]
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/token",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["token"]
            },
            "description": "Rotate the OIDC refresh token and get a new access token + ID token.\n\n**Requires:** `grant_type=refresh_token`, `refresh_token`, `client_id`\n\nThe test script automatically updates the `accessToken`, `idToken`, and `oauthRefreshToken` variables with the new rotated values."
          },
          "response": [
            {
              "name": "200 OK — Tokens rotated",
              "status": "OK",
              "code": 200,
              "header": [
                { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" },
                { "key": "Cache-Control", "value": "no-store" },
                { "key": "Pragma", "value": "no-cache" }
              ],
              "body": "{\n  \"access_token\": \"eyJhbGciOiJSUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9...\",\n  \"token_type\": \"Bearer\",\n  \"expires_in\": 3600,\n  \"refresh_token\": \"rt_rotated_xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx\",\n  \"id_token\": \"eyJhbGciOiJSUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9...\",\n  \"scope\": \"openid profile email offline_access\"\n}"
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "UserInfo",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Get UserInfo",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status is 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "const res = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('Has sub claim', () => pm.expect(res).to.have.property('sub'));",
                  "pm.test('Has given_name', () => pm.expect(res).to.have.property('given_name'));",
                  "pm.test('Has family_name', () => pm.expect(res).to.have.property('family_name'));"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "auth": {
              "type": "bearer",
              "bearer": [{ "key": "token", "value": "{{accessToken}}", "type": "string" }]
            },
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/userinfo",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["userinfo"]
            },
            "description": "Returns the claims for the authenticated user corresponding to the provided access token.\n\n**Requires:** `Authorization: Bearer <access_token>`\n\n**Claims returned:** `sub`, `given_name`, `family_name`\n\n> The `accessToken` collection variable is populated automatically by the Token requests."
          },
          "response": [
            {
              "name": "200 OK",
              "status": "OK",
              "code": 200,
              "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
              "body": "{\n  \"sub\": \"uuid-here\",\n  \"given_name\": \"Jane\",\n  \"family_name\": \"Doe\"\n}"
            },
            {
              "name": "401 Unauthorized — Missing or invalid access token",
              "status": "Unauthorized",
              "code": 401,
              "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
              "body": "{\n  \"success\": false,\n  \"error\": {\n    \"code\": \"UNAUTHORIZED\",\n    \"message\": \"Authentication required.\"\n  }\n}"
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
